## ğŸ“¦ Features Included

### ğŸ”¹ Core Blockchain Logic
- UTXO-based transaction model
- Signature validation using public keys
- Prevention of double-spending
- Block structure and confirmation flow
- Simple append-only ledger simulation

### ğŸ”¹ Wallet Functionality
- Keypair generation
- Balance tracking using UTXO scan
- Secure transaction creation
- Automatic selection of spendable UTXOs

### ğŸ”¹ Clean & Modular Code
The project follows a separation-of-concerns design, allowing each component to remain testable and easy to extend.

---

## ğŸ“˜ Example: Creating a Transaction

```python
from ex1.wallet import Wallet
from ex1.bank import Bank

# Initialize bank & wallets
bank = Bank()
alice = Wallet()
bob = Wallet()

# Bank gives Alice an initial coin
bank.genesis(alice.public_key)

# Alice creates a signed transaction to Bob
tx = alice.create_transaction(bob.public_key)

# Bank processes the transaction and adds it to a block
bank.add_block([tx])
```

